Description:
The Ultimate In Modern Beachside Living!!
Immaculately presented and in a prized position, this elegant home is located in the popular Corinella area. The home features a spacious lounge flowing into the tiled dining area and kitchen with modern appliances and reverse cycle air conditioning. There are 3 spacious bedrooms with built-ins & carpet throughout, share bathroom. The well-appointed master suite also includes a walk-in wardrobe and ensuite, a fully functional laundry. Great size backyard fully fenced. Remote control double garage with extra space than the normal size double garage with access to the backyard complete this family-friendly home.
With the foreshore at the end of the street, walking tracks & Corinella boat ramp only minutes away this home delivers a premium coastal lifestyle. Easy access to the General Store, Fig In The Bay café Restaurant, Park, Community Centre, Tennis Courts, Primary School, Early Learning Child Care Hub, and all that the Bass Coast has to offer in a great coastal lifestyle.
Inspection is a must on this property.
Strict health and safety measures are in place when viewing the property.

Contact Daniel or Tamara Leskie to arrange your private inspection or live streamed virtual inspection

Description:
Spectacular coastal retreat
Open For Inspections - You Must Register. Limited People Viewing
COVID -19
Have you or anyone whom you have been in contact, been diagnosed with COVID-19
Full Names, Addresses with Photo ID must be sent to Sales Agent 0437441127 Prior to viewing this property
Luxury acreage on the coast
Just under 90 minutes from Melbourne, this sublime coastal property measuring 8 acres (approx.) features access to your private waterfront and a recently completed, luxurious, 4-bedroom home. Finished in a sublime patina of neutral tones, the polished concrete floors support a wealth of impressive touches including black brushed metal hardware and stone benchtops throughout. Each element is bathed in sunlight year-round and invigorated by fresh sea breezes from the sound overlooking French Island.
Three-meter high ceilings tower over two living spaces designed for multi-age enjoyment with wide decking surrounding the entire home that's accessible from every room. The kitchen anchors open-plan living and is appointed with quality appliances as well as a butler's pantry. A second living is quieted beyond a study or fifth bedroom with direct access from the remote double lock-up garage.
The generous master suite comprises a large walk-in-robe with custom cabinetry and en suite whilst the zoned family bedrooms share a bathroom and separate powder room. With two bedrooms featuring large walk-in-robes, this property makes an ideal weekend retreat or lifestyle change for families who cherish the marvellous outdoors and attractions of the Bass Coast.
Highlights
· Breath-taking eight acres on the water
· Views to French Island
· New four bedroom home plus study
· Two separate living areas
· Gourmet kitchen with butler's pantry
· Superb master retreat with WIR & en suite
· Luxe finishes throughout
· Access to private beach
· NBN
· Chicken coop & run
· Tank & bore water
· Remote

Description:
15 Acres of Evolving Land
Endless potential and quaint country charm await you!
Situated in the evolving town of Lang Lang on just over 15 acres (approx.) your country change awaits you.
Conveniently located on a corner allotment, with lush, cleared land this property is ready and waiting for you to make your own personal touches and create your own country living dream. The current cottage dwelling consists of an open plan kitchen, meals and living area, and then an adjoining room with partitioned bedrooms, all complete with a bathroom and ample storage. A laundry is in the adjoining storage shed complete with an outdoor kitchen.
The lush, green outlook consists of an orchard with a variety of Fruit and Nut Trees and well-established Grape Vines. Enough room for Horses, Cattle, Sheep, Chickens the possibilities are endless!
Located proximity to the Bass Highway, an easy drive to Pakenham and Surrounds what more could you ever want or need.
Opportunities do not come up like this very often. Inspection is a must to truly appreciate this amazing outlook. Contact Amanda 0409 009 887 today to inspect without delay.
**IMPORTANT NOTICE REGARDING COVID-19:
Please check our guidelines before attending open for inspections, auctions, or our offices.
Visit: www.barryplant.com.au/media-hub/resources for the Information.
We can provide alternatives to meeting in person and for inspections, please contact us to find out what options are available to you.**

Description:
Corinella Waterfront at its best!
SWORN VALUATION IS AVAILABLE
7388 square metres (approx.) of sub dividable beach front land (STCA)
109 metres of beach front!
UNINTERRUPTED WATER VIEWS AVAILABLE FROM ALL BLOCKS ON THIS POTENTIAL SUBDIVISION (STCA)
4 bedrooms/2 bathrooms/4 car garages
This property enjoys uninterrupted views of Western Port Bay and is identified as a unique opportunity for potential redevelopment (STCA).
A near rectangular level allotment of 7,388 m2 (approx.). The land is adequately drained with no landfill and has direct street access. The property includes a 4 bedroom and 2-bathroom dwelling, fencing plus rural standard sheds and enjoys 109 metres of uninterrupted Water frontage to Westernport Bay. For those who dream, your own private oasis!.
Property can be subdivided (STCA) in accordance with the zoning, whilst maintaining neighbourhood character
No vegetation protection overlay
Construction up to 7 metres is permitted
Prestigious homes are already under construction on subdivisions adjacent to this land
There has not been another development opportunity transacted in the last 24 months within a 25-kilometre radius, that enjoys similar zoning, bay frontage and subdivision and development potential (STCA).
Enjoy as is or are you looking at a major development opportunity in Corinella Victorias best kept coastal secret. With a rural seaside location and gentle pace of life, the laid-back character of the region provides for relaxed holidays, a peaceful retirement, a stress-free lifestyle or just a better quality of life.
Overlooking Westernport Bay with walking tracks along the coastline and views to French island. This really is the perfect place to call home.

Description:
Impressive Coastal Property!!
WE ARE ACTIVE FOR APPRAISALS AND INSPECTIONS.
Youll get more for your money with all the additional features this home has to offer!!!
Including but not limited to:
Heritage Architraves and Solid Feature timber doors
High ceilings
Double glazed windows in the master bedroom
Security doors and locks on all windows
Ducted Heating and Evaporative Cooling
7kw cooling/8kw heating split system inverter a/c
22 solar panels installed / 5kw Fronious inverter with Wi-Fi tracking system
Garden shed
Fully fenced yard with extra high fences
Internal access to double garage
Perfectly positioned in a quiet court location, this immaculately presented 3 bedroom, 2 bathroom home calls to the most fastidious buyer.
There is nothing to do but move in and start enjoying life in the bayside town of Grantville.
The Kialla Homes built house is under 2 years old and has been very well maintained, offering neutral tones, tiled flooring and quality fittings throughout. Two generous bedrooms have carpet and built in robes and the master includes a large walk in robe and ensuite with his/her vanities and a glass framed double shower recess. The centrally positioned family bathroom is generous in size with a full bath, toilet and matching glass framed shower. An open plan living space full of natural light is based around the kitchen that is designed to keep you in touch with family and guests. With stainless steel appliances, a 900mm dual cooking setup, stone benchtops, dishwasher and double sink set into a large island bench with added power points, there is plenty of inspiration to make that perfect meal. Glass sliding doors lead you out to the undercover patio where you can spend more time entertaining and less time maintaining. With an automated sprinkler system in place hooked up to a water tank your low maintenance, landscaped gardens can look lovely all year round.
This property really is a must to inspect and will not be on the market for long!
Within walking distance to Grantville and amenities on offer including chemist, permanent doctor, post office, cafes, bakery and beachside walks. Dual lane Bass Highway nearby makes travelling easy to major shopping precincts at Wonthaggi or Cranbourne and Phillip Island and all its famous attractions is a mere 25 minutes drive.

Description:
GIPPSLAND'S BEST COUNTRY
Situated on some of the best country in Gippsland this 50 acre 20.26 hector property is a rare find. The property is divided into 5 paddocks. There is water to all paddocks via mains, feed troughs and dams throughout the property. Bass boasts reliable rain fall and property is quite flat.
The house block has town water, power and two road frontages. The house is in need of renovations, there are 2 garages and a large workshop with a toilet and shower.
Near new internal fencing, two hot wire top bard and middle plain new galvanized gates.
A quality block of land in this highly desired area just 15 mins to San Remo, 3 minutes to Bass which has strong local community. Only 1.5 hours from Melbourne this could be the prefect property

Description:
Lifestyle and Location Corinella!!
The location, position of this home is one of the key attractions On entering the much- loved home, you will immediately envisage yourself living the life here in Corinella.
Centrally located to the foreshore and surrounded by coastal trees, this home is located in one of Corinellas most favorite and sought-after positions for its privacy and proximity to the water.
The home features an open plan living area, a well-appointed kitchen flows through to the dining and then onto the undercover balcony, you will instantly imagine yourself entertaining all your friends and family overlooking the garden and water views.
Three bedrooms serviced by a central bathroom upstairs, the separate bottom level of the property offers a living room, potentially another bedroom or studio, this space could work as a great addition to take advantage of the high demands in the holiday rental market or to run a family business from home. Savvy buyers will see whats on offer here.
This home and location are the perfect spot for the quieter life, tranquillity, and comfortability of this home.
Open for inspections are allowed. Strict health and safety measures are in place.
To arrange to view this property for a 101 private inspection or a live video walkthrough please call Daniel or Tamara
